---

## Required Images

Place these images in `public/images/`. They come from the starter package provided by your instructor:

| File             | Used in            |
|------------------|--------------------|
| `banner.jpg`     | Hero section       |
| `small-suv.jpg`  | Upgrades grid      |
| `truck.jpg`      | Upgrades grid      |
| `sedan.jpg`      | Upgrades grid      |
| `sports-car.jpg` | Upgrades grid      |

---

## Setup & Run

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Start development server
npm run dev

# 3. Open in browser
http://localhost:5500
```

---

## Assignment Checklist

- [x] EJS partials: `head`, `header`, `navigation`, `footer`
- [x] `index.ejs` home view with hero, reviews, and upgrades sections
- [x] EJS layout wrapping all views
- [x] External CSS only вЂ” no inline styles
- [x] Mobile-first CSS (base styles for mobile, media queries for larger screens)
- [x] Responsive вЂ” no horizontal scrolling on any device
- [x] Skip-to-content link for keyboard/screen reader accessibility
- [x] `media="screen"` on CSS `<link>` element
- [x] Semantic HTML5 elements (`header`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, `article`, `footer`, `blockquote`, `cite`)
- [x] ARIA labels on interactive and landmark elements
- [x] Color contrast passes WCAG AA (navy #1a3a5c on white, gold #c8960c on dark navy)
- [x] Route handler in `routes/static.js` в†’ `controllers/baseController.js`
- [x] Server runs on `localhost:5500`